ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would suggest this course to others because it promotes healthy discussion of published materials.
I think it is a good way to take an in depth look at various concepts of cell biology. While it cannot be comprehensive, it does a good job of highlighting major areas of study.

I would recommend this class to other cell biology students, as well as those who may not have the most extensive cell biology background because the discussions in class and the interactions with instructors who are experts in these areas can help guide you through unfamiliar territory.Each week we discussed one or two papers and the discussions for several weeks would be focused on a particular area (i.e. the endocytic pathway). Students took turns leading discussions with the help of instructors. Each week a one-page summary of the reading was required.
I would summarize as in Question 1.Yes, I would recommend it because I am glad I took it.
Yes I would recommend this course.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Helps me become familiarized with techniques necessary for my work.
It helped deepen my knowledge in a couple main ways:1. Reading papers rigorously and being able to discuss them.2. Understanding current problems and techniques used in a variety of fields.
This taught me many cell bio techniques whichis helpful since I am joining a cell bio lab.
